      "content": "\"accidental inclusion in an internal test\" sounds a bit shaky if they start digging into the S3 logs, doesn't it? if a tech reporter asks why the bucket was public for three days, saying \"it was a test\" might look like we're covering up a mistake. can we frame it as something more systematic? like, can we make it sound like part of a planned migration or something so it doesn't look like we just messed up?",
